item.title: SLC Cache Sizes & SYSmark 2018
item.description: Whole-Drive Fill: Testing SLC Cache Size Most modern drives, in order to accelerate writing speed, designate a part of the drive as an 'SLC cache'. This is part of the storage that acts in 'single bit-per-cell' mode, which allows for faster reads and writes. The reason why it isn't used across the whole drive is that it doesn't allow as much data to be stored in the same area (TLC is three bits per cell, so 3x the density).

item.title: Why my Kenmore washer will not spin?
item.description: Answer If the washer would not spin or agitate, the drive belt should be checked. The washer will not spin or agitate properly if the belt is broken or if it is not tightly wound around the pulleys. If the washer will not spin, it is possible that the lid switch assembly is faulty. If the washer will not spin or agitate, it is possible that the stator assembly has burned out.
